  <p class="verse">Isaiah 43:10</p>
  <p class="verse">“You are My witnesses,” declares the LORD, “and My servant whom I have chosen, <br>so that you may know and believe Me and understand that I am He. <br><strong>Before Me no god was formed, nor will there be one after Me.”</strong></p>

  <h2 style="color:var(--blue);margin-top:2.5rem">Jesus Is Not God – </h2>
  <p>
    Even the proof-texts Christianity relies upon, when read in context and in the
    original languages, do not proclaim a deity of the Nazarene. Isaiah 43:10
    explicitly states that no divine being was formed before or after the One Creator.
    The Jewish Bible never retrofits a triune godhead; that concept arrives centuries
    later through Hellenistic theology. A candid, unbiased reading of the Tanakh
    consistently affirms absolute, indivisible monotheism—exactly what we promote here.
  </p>

